105//===========================================================================
106// returns the surface area of the given face
107//
108// Parameter: -
109// Returns: -
110// Changes Globals: -
111//===========================================================================
112float AAS_FaceArea(aas_face_t *face)
113{
114 int i, edgenum, side;
115 float total;
116 vec_t *v;
117 vec3_t d1, d2, cross;
118 aas_edge_t *edge;
119
120 edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge];
121 side = edgenum < 0;
122 edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
123 v = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]];
124
125 total = 0;
126 for (i = 1; i < face->numedges - 1; i++)
127 {
128 edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge + i];
129 side = edgenum < 0;
130 edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
131 VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]], v, d1);
132 VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[!side]], v, d2);
133 CrossProduct(d1, d2, cross);
134 total += 0.5 * VectorLength(cross);
135 } //end for
136 return total;
137} //end of the function AAS_FaceArea
138//===========================================================================
139// returns the volume of an area
140//
141// Parameter: -
142// Returns: -
143// Changes Globals: -
144//===========================================================================
145float AAS_AreaVolume(int areanum)
146{
147 int i, edgenum, facenum, side;
148 vec_t d, a, volume;
149 vec3_t corner;
150 aas_plane_t *plane;
151 aas_edge_t *edge;
152 aas_face_t *face;
153 aas_area_t *area;
154
155 area = &aasworld.areas[areanum];
156 facenum = aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface];
157 face = &aasworld.faces[abs(facenum)];
158 edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge];
159 edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
160 //
161 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]], corner);
162
163 //make tetrahedrons to all other faces
164 volume = 0;
165 for (i = 0; i < area->numfaces; i++)
166 {
167 facenum = abs(aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + i]);
168 face = &aasworld.faces[facenum];
169 side = face->backarea != areanum;
170 plane = &aasworld.planes[face->planenum ^ side];
171 d = -(DotProduct (corner, plane->normal) - plane->dist);
172 a = AAS_FaceArea(face);
173 volume += d * a;
174 } //end for
175
176 volume /= 3;
177 return volume;
178} //end of the function AAS_AreaVolume

185int AAS_BestReachableLinkArea(aas_link_t *areas)
186{
187 aas_link_t *link;
188
189 for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
190 {
191 if (AAS_AreaGrounded(link->areanum) || AAS_AreaSwim(link->areanum))
192 {
193 return link->areanum;
194 } //end if
195 } //end for
196 //
197 for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
198 {
199 if (link->areanum) return link->areanum;
200 //FIXME: this is a bad idea when the reachability is not yet
201 // calculated when the level items are loaded
202 if (AAS_AreaReachability(link->areanum))
203 return link->areanum;
204 } //end for
205 return 0;
206} //end of the function AAS_BestReachableLinkArea

213int AAS_GetJumpPadInfo(int ent, vec3_t areastart, vec3_t absmins, vec3_t absmaxs, vec3_t velocity)
214{
215 int modelnum, ent2;
216 float speed, height, gravity, time, dist, forward;
217 vec3_t origin, angles, teststart, ent2origin;
218 aas_trace_t trace;
219 char model[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
220 char target[MAX_EPAIRKEY], targetname[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
221
222 //
223 AAS_FloatForBSPEpairKey(ent, "speed", &speed);
224 if (!speed) speed = 1000;
225 VectorClear(angles);
226 //get the mins, maxs and origin of the model
227 AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "model", model, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
228 if (model[0]) modelnum = atoi(model+1);
229 else modelnum = 0;
230 AAS_BSPModelMinsMaxsOrigin(modelnum, angles, absmins, absmaxs, origin);
231 VectorAdd(origin, absmins, absmins);
232 VectorAdd(origin, absmaxs, absmaxs);
233 VectorAdd(absmins, absmaxs, origin);
234 VectorScale (origin, 0.5, origin);
235
236 //get the start areas
237 VectorCopy(origin, teststart);
238 teststart[2] += 64;
239 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(teststart, origin, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
240 if (trace.startsolid)
241 {
242 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push start solid\n");
243 VectorCopy(origin, areastart);
244 } //end if
245 else
246 {
247 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, areastart);
248 } //end else
249 areastart[2] += 0.125;
250 //
251 //AAS_DrawPermanentCross(origin, 4, 4);
252 //get the target entity
253 AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
254 for (ent2 = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent2; ent2 = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent2))
255 {
256 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent2, "targetname", targetname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
257 if (!strcmp(targetname, target)) break;
258 } //end for
259 if (!ent2)
260 {
261 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push without target entity %s\n", target);
262 return qfalse;
263 } //end if
264 AAS_VectorForBSPEpairKey(ent2, "origin", ent2origin);
265 //
266 height = ent2origin[2] - origin[2];
267 gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
268 time = sqrt( height / ( 0.5 * gravity ) );
269 if (!time)
270 {
271 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push without time\n");
272 return qfalse;
273 } //end if
274 // set s.origin2 to the push velocity
275 VectorSubtract ( ent2origin, origin, velocity);
276 dist = VectorNormalize( velocity);
277 forward = dist / time;
278 //FIXME: why multiply by 1.1
279 forward *= 1.1f;
280 VectorScale(velocity, forward, velocity);
281 velocity[2] = time * gravity;
282 return qtrue;
283} //end of the function AAS_GetJumpPadInfo

290int AAS_BestReachableFromJumpPadArea(vec3_t origin, vec3_t mins, vec3_t maxs)
291{
292 int ent, bot_visualizejumppads, bestareanum;
293 float volume, bestareavolume;
294 vec3_t areastart, cmdmove, bboxmins, bboxmaxs;
295 vec3_t absmins, absmaxs, velocity;
296 aas_clientmove_t move;
297 aas_link_t *areas, *link;
298 char classname[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
299
300#ifdef BSPC
301 bot_visualizejumppads = 0;
302#else
303 bot_visualizejumppads = LibVarValue("bot_visualizejumppads", "0");
304#endif
305 VectorAdd(origin, mins, bboxmins);
306 VectorAdd(origin, maxs, bboxmaxs);
307 for (ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent; ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent))
308 {
309 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "classname", classname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
310 if (strcmp(classname, "trigger_push")) continue;
311 //
312 if (!AAS_GetJumpPadInfo(ent, areastart, absmins, absmaxs, velocity)) continue;
313 //get the areas the jump pad brush is in
314 areas = AAS_LinkEntityClientBBox(absmins, absmaxs, -1, PRESENCE_CROUCH);
315 for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
316 {
317 if (AAS_AreaJumpPad(link->areanum)) break;
318 } //end for
319 if (!link)
320 {
321 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push not in any jump pad area\n");
322 AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
323 continue;
324 } //end if
325 //
326 //botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "found a trigger_push with velocity %f %f %f\n", velocity[0], velocity[1], velocity[2]);
327 //
328 VectorSet(cmdmove, 0, 0, 0);
329 Com_Memset(&move, 0, sizeof(aas_clientmove_t));
330 AAS_ClientMovementHitBBox(&move, -1, areastart, PRESENCE_NORMAL, qfalse,
331 velocity, cmdmove, 0, 30, 0.1f, bboxmins, bboxmaxs, bot_visualizejumppads);
332 if (move.frames < 30)
333 {
334 bestareanum = 0;
335 bestareavolume = 0;
336 for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
337 {
338 if (!AAS_AreaJumpPad(link->areanum)) continue;
339 volume = AAS_AreaVolume(link->areanum);
340 if (volume >= bestareavolume)
341 {
342 bestareanum = link->areanum;
343 bestareavolume = volume;
344 } //end if
345 } //end if
346 AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
347 return bestareanum;
348 } //end if
349 AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
350 } //end for
351 return 0;
352} //end of the function AAS_BestReachableFromJumpPadArea
353//===========================================================================

359int AAS_BestReachableArea(vec3_t origin, vec3_t mins, vec3_t maxs, vec3_t goalorigin)
360{
361 int areanum, i, j, k, l;
362 aas_link_t *areas;
363 vec3_t absmins, absmaxs;
364 //vec3_t bbmins, bbmaxs;
365 vec3_t start, end;
366 aas_trace_t trace;
367
368 if (!aasworld.loaded)
369 {
370 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "AAS_BestReachableArea: aas not loaded\n");
371 return 0;
372 } //end if
373 //find a point in an area
374 VectorCopy(origin, start);
375 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(start);
376 //while no area found fudge around a little
377 for (i = 0; i < 5 && !areanum; i++)
378 {
379 for (j = 0; j < 5 && !areanum; j++)
380 {
381 for (k = -1; k <= 1 && !areanum; k++)
382 {
383 for (l = -1; l <= 1 && !areanum; l++)
384 {
385 VectorCopy(origin, start);
386 start[0] += (float) j * 4 * k;
387 start[1] += (float) j * 4 * l;
388 start[2] += (float) i * 4;
389 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(start);
390 } //end for
391 } //end for
392 } //end for
393 } //end for
394 //if an area was found
395 if (areanum)
396 {
397 //drop client bbox down and try again
398 VectorCopy(start, end);
399 start[2] += 0.25;
400 end[2] -= 50;
401 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
402 if (!trace.startsolid)
403 {
404 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(trace.endpos);
405 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, goalorigin);
406 //FIXME: cannot enable next line right now because the reachability
407 // does not have to be calculated when the level items are loaded
408 //if the origin is in an area with reachability
409 //if (AAS_AreaReachability(areanum)) return areanum;
410 if (areanum) return areanum;
411 } //end if
412 else
413 {
414 //it can very well happen that the AAS_PointAreaNum function tells that
415 //a point is in an area and that starting an AAS_TraceClientBBox from that
416 //point will return trace.startsolid qtrue
417#if 0
418 if (AAS_PointAreaNum(start))
419 {
420 Log_Write("point %f %f %f in area %d but trace startsolid", start[0], start[1], start[2], areanum);
421 AAS_DrawPermanentCross(start, 4, LINECOLOR_RED);
422 } //end if
423 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "AAS_BestReachableArea: start solid\n");
424#endif
425 VectorCopy(start, goalorigin);
426 return areanum;
427 } //end else
428 } //end if
429 //
430 //AAS_PresenceTypeBoundingBox(PRESENCE_CROUCH, bbmins, bbmaxs);
431 //NOTE: the goal origin does not have to be in the goal area
432 // because the bot will have to move towards the item origin anyway
433 VectorCopy(origin, goalorigin);
434 //
435 VectorAdd(origin, mins, absmins);
436 VectorAdd(origin, maxs, absmaxs);
437 //add bounding box size
438 //VectorSubtract(absmins, bbmaxs, absmins);
439 //VectorSubtract(absmaxs, bbmins, absmaxs);
440 //link an invalid (-1) entity
441 areas = AAS_LinkEntityClientBBox(absmins, absmaxs, -1, PRESENCE_CROUCH);
442 //get the reachable link arae
443 areanum = AAS_BestReachableLinkArea(areas);
444 //unlink the invalid entity
445 AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
446 //
447 return areanum;
448} //end of the function AAS_BestReachableArea

455void AAS_SetupReachabilityHeap(void)
456{
457 int i;
458
459 reachabilityheap = (aas_lreachability_t *) GetClearedMemory(
460 AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE * sizeof(aas_lreachability_t));
461 for (i = 0; i < AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE-1; i++)
462 {
463 reachabilityheap[i].next = &reachabilityheap[i+1];
464 } //end for
465 reachabilityheap[AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE-1].next = NULL;
466 nextreachability = reachabilityheap;
467 numlreachabilities = 0;
468} //end of the function AAS_InitReachabilityHeap
469//===========================================================================
470//
471// Parameter: -
472// Returns: -
473// Changes Globals: -
474//===========================================================================
475void AAS_ShutDownReachabilityHeap(void)
476{
477 FreeMemory(reachabilityheap);
478 numlreachabilities = 0;
479} //end of the function AAS_ShutDownReachabilityHeap
480//===========================================================================
481// returns a reachability link
482//
483// Parameter: -
484// Returns: -
485// Changes Globals: -
486//===========================================================================
487aas_lreachability_t *AAS_AllocReachability(void)
488{
489 aas_lreachability_t *r;
490
491 if (!nextreachability) return NULL;
492 //make sure the error message only shows up once
493 if (!nextreachability->next) AAS_Error("AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE\n");
494 //
495 r = nextreachability;
496 nextreachability = nextreachability->next;
497 numlreachabilities++;
498 return r;
499} //end of the function AAS_AllocReachability
500//===========================================================================
501// frees a reachability link
502//
503// Parameter: -
504// Returns: -
505// Changes Globals: -
506//===========================================================================
507void AAS_FreeReachability(aas_lreachability_t *lreach)
508{
509 Com_Memset(lreach, 0, sizeof(aas_lreachability_t));
510
511 lreach->next = nextreachability;
512 nextreachability = lreach;
513 numlreachabilities--;
514} //end of the function AAS_FreeReachability
515//===========================================================================

522int AAS_AreaReachability(int areanum)
523{
524 if (areanum < 0 || areanum >= aasworld.numareas)
525 {
526 AAS_Error("AAS_AreaReachability: areanum %d out of range\n", areanum);
527 return 0;
528 } //end if
529 return aasworld.areasettings[areanum].numreachableareas;
530} //end of the function AAS_AreaReachability
531//===========================================================================
532// returns the surface area of all ground faces together of the area
533//
534// Parameter: -
535// Returns: -
536// Changes Globals: -
537//===========================================================================
538float AAS_AreaGroundFaceArea(int areanum)
539{
540 int i;
541 float total;
542 aas_area_t *area;
543 aas_face_t *face;
544
545 total = 0;
546 area = &aasworld.areas[areanum];
547 for (i = 0; i < area->numfaces; i++)
548 {
549 face = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + i])];
550 if (!(face->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
551 //
552 total += AAS_FaceArea(face);
553 } //end for
554 return total;
555} //end of the function AAS_AreaGroundFaceArea
556//===========================================================================
557// returns the center of a face
558//
559// Parameter: -
560// Returns: -
561// Changes Globals: -
562//===========================================================================
563void AAS_FaceCenter(int facenum, vec3_t center)
564{
565 int i;
566 float scale;
567 aas_face_t *face;
568 aas_edge_t *edge;
569
570 face = &aasworld.faces[facenum];
571
572 VectorClear(center);
573 for (i = 0; i < face->numedges; i++)
574 {
575 edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge + i])];
576 VectorAdd(center, aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]], center);
577 VectorAdd(center, aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]], center);
578 } //end for
579 scale = 0.5 / face->numedges;
580 VectorScale(center, scale, center);
581} //end of the function AAS_FaceCenter
582//===========================================================================
583// returns the maximum distance a player can fall before being damaged
584// damage = deltavelocity*deltavelocity * 0.0001
585//
586// Parameter: -
587// Returns: -
588// Changes Globals: -
589//===========================================================================
590int AAS_FallDamageDistance(void)
591{
592 float maxzvelocity, gravity, t;
593
594 maxzvelocity = sqrt(30 * 10000);
595 gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
596 t = maxzvelocity / gravity;
597 return 0.5 * gravity * t * t;
598} //end of the function AAS_FallDamageDistance
599//===========================================================================
600// distance = 0.5 * gravity * t * t
601// vel = t * gravity
602// damage = vel * vel * 0.0001
603//
604// Parameter: -
605// Returns: -
606// Changes Globals: -
607//===========================================================================
608float AAS_FallDelta(float distance)
609{
610 float t, delta, gravity;
611
612 gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
613 t = sqrt(fabs(distance) * 2 / gravity);
614 delta = t * gravity;
615 return delta * delta * 0.0001;
616} //end of the function AAS_FallDelta
617//===========================================================================
618//
619// Parameter: -
620// Returns: -
621// Changes Globals: -
622//===========================================================================
623float AAS_MaxJumpHeight(float phys_jumpvel)
624{
625 float phys_gravity;
626
627 phys_gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
628 //maximum height a player can jump with the given initial z velocity
629 return 0.5 * phys_gravity * (phys_jumpvel / phys_gravity) * (phys_jumpvel / phys_gravity);
630} //end of the function MaxJumpHeight
631//===========================================================================
632// returns true if a player can only crouch in the area
633//
634// Parameter: -
635// Returns: -
636// Changes Globals: -
637//===========================================================================
638float AAS_MaxJumpDistance(float phys_jumpvel)
639{
640 float phys_gravity, phys_maxvelocity, t;
641
642 phys_gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
643 phys_maxvelocity = aassettings.phys_maxvelocity;
644 //time a player takes to fall the height
645 t = sqrt(aassettings.rs_maxjumpfallheight / (0.5 * phys_gravity));
646 //maximum distance
647 return phys_maxvelocity * (t + phys_jumpvel / phys_gravity);
648} //end of the function AAS_MaxJumpDistance

685//===========================================================================
686//
687// Parameter: -
688// Returns: -
689// Changes Globals: -
690//===========================================================================
691int AAS_AreaLava(int areanum)
692{
693 return (aasworld.areasettings[areanum].contents & AREACONTENTS_LAVA);

795//===========================================================================
796// returns true if there is a solid just after the end point when going
797// from start to end
798//
799// Parameter: -
800// Returns: -
801// Changes Globals: -
802//===========================================================================
803int AAS_NearbySolidOrGap(vec3_t start, vec3_t end)
804{
805 vec3_t dir, testpoint;
806 int areanum;
807
808 VectorSubtract(end, start, dir);
809 dir[2] = 0;
810 VectorNormalize(dir);
811 VectorMA(end, 48, dir, testpoint);
812
813 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(testpoint);
814 if (!areanum)
815 {
816 testpoint[2] += 16;
817 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(testpoint);
818 if (!areanum) return qtrue;
819 } //end if
820 VectorMA(end, 64, dir, testpoint);
821 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(testpoint);
822 if (areanum)
823 {
824 if (!AAS_AreaSwim(areanum) && !AAS_AreaGrounded(areanum)) return qtrue;
825 } //end if
826 return qfalse;
827} //end of the function AAS_SolidGapTime
828//===========================================================================
829// searches for swim reachabilities between adjacent areas
830//
831// Parameter: -
832// Returns: -
833// Changes Globals: -
834//===========================================================================
835int AAS_Reachability_Swim(int area1num, int area2num)
836{
837 int i, j, face1num, face2num, side1;
838 aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
839 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
840 aas_face_t *face1;
841 aas_plane_t *plane;
842 vec3_t start;
843
844 if (!AAS_AreaSwim(area1num) || !AAS_AreaSwim(area2num)) return qfalse;
845 //if the second area is crouch only
846 if (!(aasworld.areasettings[area2num].presencetype & PRESENCE_NORMAL)) return qfalse;
847
848 area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
849 area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
850
851 //if the areas are not near enough
852 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
853 {
854 if (area1->mins[i] > area2->maxs[i] + 10) return qfalse;
855 if (area1->maxs[i] < area2->mins[i] - 10) return qfalse;
856 } //end for
857 //find a shared face and create a reachability link
858 for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
859 {
860 face1num = aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i];
861 side1 = face1num < 0;
862 face1num = abs(face1num);
863 //
864 for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
865 {
866 face2num = abs(aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j]);
867 //
868 if (face1num == face2num)
869 {
870 AAS_FaceCenter(face1num, start);
871 //
872 if (AAS_PointContents(start) & (CONTENTS_LAVA|CONTENTS_SLIME|CONTENTS_WATER))
873 {
874 //
875 face1 = &aasworld.faces[face1num];
876 //create a new reachability link
877 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
878 if (!lreach) return qfalse;
879 lreach->areanum = area2num;
880 lreach->facenum = face1num;
881 lreach->edgenum = 0;
882 VectorCopy(start, lreach->start);
883 plane = &aasworld.planes[face1->planenum ^ side1];
884 VectorMA(lreach->start, -INSIDEUNITS, plane->normal, lreach->end);
885 lreach->traveltype = TRAVEL_SWIM;
886 lreach->traveltime = 1;
887 //if the volume of the area is rather small
888 if (AAS_AreaVolume(area2num) < 800)
889 lreach->traveltime += 200;
890 //if (!(AAS_PointContents(start) & MASK_WATER)) lreach->traveltime += 500;
891 //link the reachability
892 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
893 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
894 reach_swim++;
895 return qtrue;
896 } //end if
897 } //end if
898 } //end for
899 } //end for
900 return qfalse;
901} //end of the function AAS_Reachability_Swim
902//===========================================================================
903// searches for reachabilities between adjacent areas with equal floor
904// heights
905//
906// Parameter: -
907// Returns: -
908// Changes Globals: -
909//===========================================================================
910int AAS_Reachability_EqualFloorHeight(int area1num, int area2num)
911{
912 int i, j, edgenum, edgenum1, edgenum2, foundreach, side;
913 float height, bestheight, length, bestlength;
914 vec3_t dir, start, end, normal, invgravity, gravitydirection = {0, 0, -1};
915 vec3_t edgevec;
916 aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
917 aas_face_t *face1, *face2;
918 aas_edge_t *edge;
919 aas_plane_t *plane2;
920 aas_lreachability_t lr, *lreach;
921
922 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) || !AAS_AreaGrounded(area2num)) return qfalse;
923
924 area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
925 area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
926 //if the areas are not near enough in the x-y direction
927 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
928 {
929 if (area1->mins[i] > area2->maxs[i] + 10) return qfalse;
930 if (area1->maxs[i] < area2->mins[i] - 10) return qfalse;
931 } //end for
932 //if area 2 is too high above area 1
933 if (area2->mins[2] > area1->maxs[2]) return qfalse;
934 //
935 VectorCopy(gravitydirection, invgravity);
936 VectorInverse(invgravity);
937 //
938 bestheight = 99999;
939 bestlength = 0;
940 foundreach = qfalse;
941 Com_Memset(&lr, 0, sizeof(aas_lreachability_t)); //make the compiler happy
942 //
943 //check if the areas have ground faces with a common edge
944 //if existing use the lowest common edge for a reachability link
945 for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
946 {
947 face1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i])];
948 if (!(face1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
949 //
950 for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
951 {
952 face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j])];
953 if (!(face2->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
954 //if there is a common edge
955 for (edgenum1 = 0; edgenum1 < face1->numedges; edgenum1++)
956 {
957 for (edgenum2 = 0; edgenum2 < face2->numedges; edgenum2++)
958 {
959 if (abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + edgenum1]) !=
960 abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge + edgenum2]))
961 continue;
962 edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + edgenum1];
963 side = edgenum < 0;
964 edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
965 //get the length of the edge
966 VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]],
967 aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]], dir);
968 length = VectorLength(dir);
969 //get the start point
970 VectorAdd(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]],
971 aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]], start);
972 VectorScale(start, 0.5, start);
973 VectorCopy(start, end);
974 //get the end point several units inside area2
975 //and the start point several units inside area1
976 //NOTE: normal is pointing into area2 because the
977 //face edges are stored counter clockwise
978 VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]],
979 aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[!side]], edgevec);
980 plane2 = &aasworld.planes[face2->planenum];
981 CrossProduct(edgevec, plane2->normal, normal);
982 VectorNormalize(normal);
983 //
984 //VectorMA(start, -1, normal, start);
985 VectorMA(end, INSIDEUNITS_WALKEND, normal, end);
986 VectorMA(start, INSIDEUNITS_WALKSTART, normal, start);
987 end[2] += 0.125;
988 //
989 height = DotProduct(invgravity, start);
990 //NOTE: if there's nearby solid or a gap area after this area
991 //disabled this crap
992 //if (AAS_NearbySolidOrGap(start, end)) height += 200;
993 //NOTE: disabled because it disables reachabilities to very small areas
994 //if (AAS_PointAreaNum(end) != area2num) continue;
995 //get the longest lowest edge
996 if (height < bestheight ||
997 (height < bestheight + 1 && length > bestlength))
998 {
999 bestheight = height;
1000 bestlength = length;
1001 //create a new reachability link
1002 lr.areanum = area2num;
1003 lr.facenum = 0;
1004 lr.edgenum = edgenum;
1005 VectorCopy(start, lr.start);
1006 VectorCopy(end, lr.end);
1007 lr.traveltype = TRAVEL_WALK;
1008 lr.traveltime = 1;
1009 foundreach = qtrue;
1010 } //end if
1011 } //end for
1012 } //end for
1013 } //end for
1014 } //end for
1015 if (foundreach)
1016 {
1017 //create a new reachability link
1018 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
1019 if (!lreach) return qfalse;
1020 lreach->areanum = lr.areanum;
1021 lreach->facenum = lr.facenum;
1022 lreach->edgenum = lr.edgenum;
1023 VectorCopy(lr.start, lreach->start);
1024 VectorCopy(lr.end, lreach->end);
1025 lreach->traveltype = lr.traveltype;
1026 lreach->traveltime = lr.traveltime;
1027 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
1028 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
1029 //if going into a crouch area
1030 if (!AAS_AreaCrouch(area1num) && AAS_AreaCrouch(area2num))
1031 {
1032 lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_startcrouch;
1033 } //end if
1034 /*
1035 //NOTE: if there's nearby solid or a gap area after this area
1036 if (!AAS_NearbySolidOrGap(lreach->start, lreach->end))
1037 {
1038 lreach->traveltime += 100;
1039 } //end if
1040 */
1041 //avoid rather small areas
1042 //if (AAS_AreaGroundFaceArea(lreach->areanum) < 500) lreach->traveltime += 100;
1043 //
1044 reach_equalfloor++;
1045 return qtrue;
1046 } //end if
1047 return qfalse;
1048} //end of the function AAS_Reachability_EqualFloorHeight
1049//===========================================================================
1050// searches step, barrier, waterjump and walk off ledge reachabilities
1051//
1052// Parameter: -
1053// Returns: -
1054// Changes Globals: -
1055//===========================================================================
1056int AAS_Reachability_Step_Barrier_WaterJump_WalkOffLedge(int area1num, int area2num)
1057{
1058 int i, j, k, l, edge1num, edge2num, areas[10], numareas;
1059 int ground_bestarea2groundedgenum, ground_foundreach;
1060 int water_bestarea2groundedgenum, water_foundreach;
1061 int side1, area1swim, faceside1, groundface1num;
1062 float dist, dist1, dist2, diff, ortdot;
1063 //float invgravitydot;
1064 float x1, x2, x3, x4, y1, y2, y3, y4, tmp, y;
1065 float length, ground_bestlength, water_bestlength, ground_bestdist, water_bestdist;
1066 vec3_t v1, v2, v3, v4, tmpv, p1area1, p1area2, p2area1, p2area2;
1067 vec3_t normal, ort, edgevec, start, end, dir;
1068 vec3_t ground_beststart = {0, 0, 0}, ground_bestend = {0, 0, 0}, ground_bestnormal = {0, 0, 0};
1069 vec3_t water_beststart = {0, 0, 0}, water_bestend = {0, 0, 0}, water_bestnormal = {0, 0, 0};
1070 vec3_t invgravity = {0, 0, 1};
1071 vec3_t testpoint;
1072 aas_plane_t *plane;
1073 aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
1074 aas_face_t *groundface1, *groundface2;
1075 aas_edge_t *edge1, *edge2;
1076 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
1077 aas_trace_t trace;
1078
1079 //must be able to walk or swim in the first area
1080 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) && !AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) return qfalse;
1081 //
1082 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area2num) && !AAS_AreaSwim(area2num)) return qfalse;
1083 //
1084 area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
1085 area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
1086 //if the first area contains a liquid
1087 area1swim = AAS_AreaSwim(area1num);
1088 //if the areas are not near enough in the x-y direction
1089 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
1090 {
1091 if (area1->mins[i] > area2->maxs[i] + 10) return qfalse;
1092 if (area1->maxs[i] < area2->mins[i] - 10) return qfalse;
1093 } //end for
1094 //
1095 ground_foundreach = qfalse;
1096 ground_bestdist = 99999;
1097 ground_bestlength = 0;
1098 ground_bestarea2groundedgenum = 0;
1099 //
1100 water_foundreach = qfalse;
1101 water_bestdist = 99999;
1102 water_bestlength = 0;
1103 water_bestarea2groundedgenum = 0;
1104 //
1105 for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
1106 {
1107 groundface1num = aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i];
1108 faceside1 = groundface1num < 0;
1109 groundface1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(groundface1num)];
1110 //if this isn't a ground face
1111 if (!(groundface1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND))
1112 {
1113 //if we can swim in the first area
1114 if (area1swim)
1115 {
1116 //face plane must be more or less horizontal
1117 plane = &aasworld.planes[groundface1->planenum ^ (!faceside1)];
1118 if (DotProduct(plane->normal, invgravity) < 0.7) continue;
1119 } //end if
1120 else
1121 {
1122 //if we can't swim in the area it must be a ground face
1123 continue;
1124 } //end else
1125 } //end if
1126 //
1127 for (k = 0; k < groundface1->numedges; k++)
1128 {
1129 edge1num = aasworld.edgeindex[groundface1->firstedge + k];
1130 side1 = (edge1num < 0);
1131 //NOTE: for water faces we must take the side area 1 is
1132 // on into account because the face is shared and doesn't
1133 // have to be oriented correctly
1134 if (!(groundface1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) side1 = (side1 == faceside1);
1135 edge1num = abs(edge1num);
1136 edge1 = &aasworld.edges[edge1num];
1137 //vertexes of the edge
1138 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge1->v[!side1]], v1);
1139 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge1->v[side1]], v2);
1140 //get a vertical plane through the edge
1141 //NOTE: normal is pointing into area 2 because the
1142 //face edges are stored counter clockwise
1143 VectorSubtract(v2, v1, edgevec);
1144 CrossProduct(edgevec, invgravity, normal);
1145 VectorNormalize(normal);
1146 dist = DotProduct(normal, v1);
1147 //check the faces from the second area
1148 for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
1149 {
1150 groundface2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j])];
1151 //must be a ground face
1152 if (!(groundface2->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
1153 //check the edges of this ground face
1154 for (l = 0; l < groundface2->numedges; l++)
1155 {
1156 edge2num = abs(aasworld.edgeindex[groundface2->firstedge + l]);
1157 edge2 = &aasworld.edges[edge2num];
1158 //vertexes of the edge
1159 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge2->v[0]], v3);
1160 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge2->v[1]], v4);
1161 //check the distance between the two points and the vertical plane
1162 //through the edge of area1
1163 diff = DotProduct(normal, v3) - dist;
1164 if (diff < -0.1 || diff > 0.1) continue;
1165 diff = DotProduct(normal, v4) - dist;
1166 if (diff < -0.1 || diff > 0.1) continue;
1167 //
1168 //project the two ground edges into the step side plane
1169 //and calculate the shortest distance between the two
1170 //edges if they overlap in the direction orthogonal to
1171 //the gravity direction
1172 CrossProduct(invgravity, normal, ort);
1173 //invgravitydot = DotProduct(invgravity, invgravity);
1174 ortdot = DotProduct(ort, ort);
1175 //projection into the step plane
1176 //NOTE: since gravity is vertical this is just the z coordinate
1177 y1 = v1[2];//DotProduct(v1, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1178 y2 = v2[2];//DotProduct(v2, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1179 y3 = v3[2];//DotProduct(v3, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1180 y4 = v4[2];//DotProduct(v4, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1181 //
1182 x1 = DotProduct(v1, ort) / ortdot;
1183 x2 = DotProduct(v2, ort) / ortdot;
1184 x3 = DotProduct(v3, ort) / ortdot;
1185 x4 = DotProduct(v4, ort) / ortdot;
1186 //
1187 if (x1 > x2)
1188 {
1189 tmp = x1; x1 = x2; x2 = tmp;
1190 tmp = y1; y1 = y2; y2 = tmp;
1191 VectorCopy(v1, tmpv); VectorCopy(v2, v1); VectorCopy(tmpv, v2);
1192 } //end if
1193 if (x3 > x4)
1194 {
1195 tmp = x3; x3 = x4; x4 = tmp;
1196 tmp = y3; y3 = y4; y4 = tmp;
1197 VectorCopy(v3, tmpv); VectorCopy(v4, v3); VectorCopy(tmpv, v4);
1198 } //end if
1199 //if the two projected edge lines have no overlap
1200 if (x2 <= x3 || x4 <= x1)
1201 {
1202// Log_Write("lines no overlap: from area %d to %d\r\n", area1num, area2num);
1203 continue;
1204 } //end if
1205 //if the two lines fully overlap
1206 if ((x1 - 0.5 < x3 && x4 < x2 + 0.5) &&
1207 (x3 - 0.5 < x1 && x2 < x4 + 0.5))
1208 {
1209 dist1 = y3 - y1;
1210 dist2 = y4 - y2;
1211 VectorCopy(v1, p1area1);
1212 VectorCopy(v2, p2area1);
1213 VectorCopy(v3, p1area2);
1214 VectorCopy(v4, p2area2);
1215 } //end if
1216 else
1217 {
1218 //if the points are equal
1219 if (x1 > x3 - 0.1 && x1 < x3 + 0.1)
1220 {
1221 dist1 = y3 - y1;
1222 VectorCopy(v1, p1area1);
1223 VectorCopy(v3, p1area2);
1224 } //end if
1225 else if (x1 < x3)
1226 {
1227 y = y1 + (x3 - x1) * (y2 - y1) / (x2 - x1);
1228 dist1 = y3 - y;
1229 VectorCopy(v3, p1area1);
1230 p1area1[2] = y;
1231 VectorCopy(v3, p1area2);
1232 } //end if
1233 else
1234 {
1235 y = y3 + (x1 - x3) * (y4 - y3) / (x4 - x3);
1236 dist1 = y - y1;
1237 VectorCopy(v1, p1area1);
1238 VectorCopy(v1, p1area2);
1239 p1area2[2] = y;
1240 } //end if
1241 //if the points are equal
1242 if (x2 > x4 - 0.1 && x2 < x4 + 0.1)
1243 {
1244 dist2 = y4 - y2;
1245 VectorCopy(v2, p2area1);
1246 VectorCopy(v4, p2area2);
1247 } //end if
1248 else if (x2 < x4)
1249 {
1250 y = y3 + (x2 - x3) * (y4 - y3) / (x4 - x3);
1251 dist2 = y - y2;
1252 VectorCopy(v2, p2area1);
1253 VectorCopy(v2, p2area2);
1254 p2area2[2] = y;
1255 } //end if
1256 else
1257 {
1258 y = y1 + (x4 - x1) * (y2 - y1) / (x2 - x1);
1259 dist2 = y4 - y;
1260 VectorCopy(v4, p2area1);
1261 p2area1[2] = y;
1262 VectorCopy(v4, p2area2);
1263 } //end else
1264 } //end else
1265 //if both distances are pretty much equal
1266 //then we take the middle of the points
1267 if (dist1 > dist2 - 1 && dist1 < dist2 + 1)
1268 {
1269 dist = dist1;
1270 VectorAdd(p1area1, p2area1, start);
1271 VectorScale(start, 0.5, start);
1272 VectorAdd(p1area2, p2area2, end);
1273 VectorScale(end, 0.5, end);
1274 } //end if
1275 else if (dist1 < dist2)
1276 {
1277 dist = dist1;
1278 VectorCopy(p1area1, start);
1279 VectorCopy(p1area2, end);
1280 } //end else if
1281 else
1282 {
1283 dist = dist2;
1284 VectorCopy(p2area1, start);
1285 VectorCopy(p2area2, end);
1286 } //end else
1287 //get the length of the overlapping part of the edges of the two areas
1288 VectorSubtract(p2area2, p1area2, dir);
1289 length = VectorLength(dir);
1290 //
1291 if (groundface1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)
1292 {
1293 //if the vertical distance is smaller
1294 if (dist < ground_bestdist ||
1295 //or the vertical distance is pretty much the same
1296 //but the overlapping part of the edges is longer
1297 (dist < ground_bestdist + 1 && length > ground_bestlength))

1300 ground_bestlength = length;

1307 //best point towards area2
1308 VectorCopy(end, ground_bestend);
1309 } //end if
1310 } //end if

1313 //if the vertical distance is smaller
1314 if (dist < water_bestdist ||
1315 //or the vertical distance is pretty much the same
1316 //but the overlapping part of the edges is longer

1318 {
1319 water_bestdist = dist;
1320 water_bestlength = length;
1321 water_foundreach = qtrue;
1322 water_bestarea2groundedgenum = edge1num;
1323 //best point towards area1
1324 VectorCopy(start, water_beststart);
1325 //normal is pointing into area2
1326 VectorCopy(normal, water_bestnormal);
1327 //best point towards area2
1328 VectorCopy(end, water_bestend);
1329 } //end if
1330 } //end else
1331 } //end for
1332 } //end for
1333 } //end for
1334 } //end for

1389 } //end if
1390 } //end if

1535 reach_walk++;

1538 // if no maximum fall height set or less than the max
1539 if (!aassettings.rs_maxfallheight || fabs(ground_bestdist) < aassettings.rs_maxfallheight) {
1540 //trace a bounding box vertically to check for solids

1549 {

1581 } //end if
1582 } //end if
1583 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
1584 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
1585 //
1586 reach_walkoffledge++;
1587 //NOTE: don't create a weapon (rl, bfg) jump reachability here
1588 //because it interferes with other reachabilities
1589 //like the ladder reachability
1590 return qtrue;
1591 } //end if
1592 } //end if
1593 } //end if
1594 } //end if
1595 } //end else
1596 } //end if
1597 return qfalse;

2090//===========================================================================
2091// creates possible jump reachabilities between the areas
2092//
2093// The two closest points on the ground of the areas are calculated
2094// One of the points will be on an edge of a ground face of area1 and
2095// one on an edge of a ground face of area2.
2096// If there is a range of closest points the point in the middle of this range
2097// is selected.
2098// Between these two points there must be one or more gaps.
2099// If the gaps exist a potential jump is predicted.
2100//
2101// Parameter: -
2102// Returns: -
2103// Changes Globals: -
2104//===========================================================================
2105int AAS_Reachability_Jump(int area1num, int area2num)
2106{
2107 int i, j, k, l, face1num, face2num, edge1num, edge2num, traveltype;
2108 int stopevent, areas[10], numareas;
2109 float phys_jumpvel, maxjumpdistance, maxjumpheight, height, bestdist, speed;
2110 vec_t *v1, *v2, *v3, *v4;
2111 vec3_t beststart = {0}, beststart2 = {0}, bestend = {0}, bestend2 = {0};
2112 vec3_t teststart, testend, dir, velocity, cmdmove, up = {0, 0, 1}, sidewards;
2113 aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
2114 aas_face_t *face1, *face2;
2115 aas_edge_t *edge1, *edge2;
2116 aas_plane_t *plane1, *plane2, *plane;
2117 aas_trace_t trace;
2118 aas_clientmove_t move;
2119 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
2120
2121 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) || !AAS_AreaGrounded(area2num)) return qfalse;
2122 //cannot jump from or to a crouch area
2123 if (AAS_AreaCrouch(area1num) || AAS_AreaCrouch(area2num)) return qfalse;
2124 //
2125 area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
2126 area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
2127 //

2129 //maximum distance a player can jump
2130 maxjumpdistance = 2 * AAS_MaxJumpDistance(phys_jumpvel);
2131 //maximum height a player can jump with the given initial z velocity
2132 maxjumpheight = AAS_MaxJumpHeight(phys_jumpvel);
2133
2134 //if the areas are not near enough in the x-y direction
2135 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
2136 {
2137 if (area1->mins[i] > area2->maxs[i] + maxjumpdistance) return qfalse;
2138 if (area1->maxs[i] < area2->mins[i] - maxjumpdistance) return qfalse;
2139 } //end for
2140 //if area2 is way to high to jump up to
2141 if (area2->mins[2] > area1->maxs[2] + maxjumpheight) return qfalse;
2142 //
2143 bestdist = 999999;
2144 //
2145 for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
2146 {
2147 face1num = aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i];
2148 face1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face1num)];
2149 //if not a ground face
2150 if (!(face1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
2151 //
2152 for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
2153 {
2154 face2num = aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j];
2155 face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face2num)];
2156 //if not a ground face
2157 if (!(face2->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
2158 //
2159 for (k = 0; k < face1->numedges; k++)
2160 {
2161 edge1num = abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + k]);
2162 edge1 = &aasworld.edges[edge1num];
2163 for (l = 0; l < face2->numedges; l++)
2164 {
2165 edge2num = abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge + l]);
2166 edge2 = &aasworld.edges[edge2num];
2167 //calculate the minimum distance between the two edges
2168 v1 = aasworld.vertexes[edge1->v[0]];
2169 v2 = aasworld.vertexes[edge1->v[1]];
2170 v3 = aasworld.vertexes[edge2->v[0]];
2171 v4 = aasworld.vertexes[edge2->v[1]];
2172 //get the ground planes
2173 plane1 = &aasworld.planes[face1->planenum];
2174 plane2 = &aasworld.planes[face2->planenum];
2175 //
2176 bestdist = AAS_ClosestEdgePoints(v1, v2, v3, v4, plane1, plane2,
2177 beststart, bestend,
2178 beststart2, bestend2, bestdist);
2179 } //end for
2180 } //end for
2181 } //end for
2182 } //end for
2183 VectorMiddle(beststart, beststart2, beststart);
2184 VectorMiddle(bestend, bestend2, bestend);
2185 if (bestdist > 4 && bestdist < maxjumpdistance)
2186 {
2187// Log_Write("shortest distance between %d and %d is %f\r\n", area1num, area2num, bestdist);
2188 // if very close and almost no height difference then the bot can walk
2189 if (bestdist <= 48 && fabs(beststart[2] - bestend[2]) < 8)
2190 {
2191 speed = 400;
2192 traveltype = TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE;
2193 } //end if
2194 else if (AAS_HorizontalVelocityForJump(0, beststart, bestend, &speed))
2195 {
2196 //FIXME: why multiply with 1.2???
2197 speed *= 1.2f;
2198 traveltype = TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE;
2199 } //end else if
2200 else
2201 {
2202 //get the horizontal speed for the jump, if it isn't possible to calculate this
2203 //speed (the jump is not possible) then there's no jump reachability created
2204 if (!AAS_HorizontalVelocityForJump(phys_jumpvel, beststart, bestend, &speed))
2205 return qfalse;
2206 speed *= 1.05f;
2207 traveltype = TRAVEL_JUMP;
2208 //
2209 //NOTE: test if the horizontal distance isn't too small
2210 VectorSubtract(bestend, beststart, dir);
2211 dir[2] = 0;
2212 if (VectorLength(dir) < 10)
2213 return qfalse;
2214 } //end if
2215 //
2216 VectorSubtract(bestend, beststart, dir);
2217 VectorNormalize(dir);
2218 VectorMA(beststart, 1, dir, teststart);
2219 //
2220 VectorCopy(teststart, testend);
2221 testend[2] -= 100;
2222 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(teststart, testend, PRESENCE_NORMAL, -1);
2223 //
2224 if (trace.startsolid)
2225 return qfalse;
2226 if (trace.fraction < 1)
2227 {
2228 plane = &aasworld.planes[trace.planenum];
2229 // if the bot can stand on the surface
2230 if (DotProduct(plane->normal, up) >= 0.7)
2231 {
2232 // if no lava or slime below
2233 if (!(AAS_PointContents(trace.endpos) & (CONTENTS_LAVA|CONTENTS_SLIME)))
2234 {
2235 if (teststart[2] - trace.endpos[2] <= aassettings.phys_maxbarrier)
2236 return qfalse;
2237 } //end if
2238 } //end if
2239 } //end if
2240 //
2241 VectorMA(bestend, -1, dir, teststart);
2242 //
2243 VectorCopy(teststart, testend);
2244 testend[2] -= 100;
2245 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(teststart, testend, PRESENCE_NORMAL, -1);
2246 //
2247 if (trace.startsolid)
2248 return qfalse;
2249 if (trace.fraction < 1)
2250 {
2251 plane = &aasworld.planes[trace.planenum];
2252 // if the bot can stand on the surface
2253 if (DotProduct(plane->normal, up) >= 0.7)
2254 {
2255 // if no lava or slime below
2256 if (!(AAS_PointContents(trace.endpos) & (CONTENTS_LAVA|CONTENTS_SLIME)))
2257 {
2258 if (teststart[2] - trace.endpos[2] <= aassettings.phys_maxbarrier)
2259 return qfalse;
2260 } //end if
2261 } //end if
2262 } //end if
2263 //
2264 // get command movement
2265 VectorClear(cmdmove);
2266 if ((traveltype & TRAVELTYPE_MASK) == TRAVEL_JUMP)
2267 cmdmove[2] = aassettings.phys_jumpvel;
2268 else
2269 cmdmove[2] = 0;
2270 //
2271 VectorSubtract(bestend, beststart, dir);
2272 dir[2] = 0;
2273 VectorNormalize(dir);
2274 CrossProduct(dir, up, sidewards);
2275 //
2276 stopevent = SE_HITGROUND|SE_ENTERWATER|SE_ENTERSLIME|SE_ENTERLAVA|SE_HITGROUNDDAMAGE;
2277 if (!AAS_AreaClusterPortal(area1num) && !AAS_AreaClusterPortal(area2num))
2278 stopevent |= SE_TOUCHCLUSTERPORTAL;
2279 //
2280 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
2281 {
2282 //
2283 if (i == 1)
2284 VectorAdd(testend, sidewards, testend);
2285 else if (i == 2)
2286 VectorSubtract(bestend, sidewards, testend);
2287 else
2288 VectorCopy(bestend, testend);
2289 VectorSubtract(testend, beststart, dir);
2290 dir[2] = 0;
2291 VectorNormalize(dir);
2292 VectorScale(dir, speed, velocity);
2293 //
2294 AAS_PredictClientMovement(&move, -1, beststart, PRESENCE_NORMAL, qtrue,
2295 velocity, cmdmove, 3, 30, 0.1f,
2296 stopevent, 0, qfalse);
2297 // if prediction time wasn't enough to fully predict the movement
2298 if (move.frames >= 30)
2299 return qfalse;
2300 // don't enter slime or lava and don't fall from too high
2301 if (move.stopevent & (SE_ENTERSLIME|SE_ENTERLAVA))
2302 return qfalse;
2303 // never jump or fall through a cluster portal
2304 if (move.stopevent & SE_TOUCHCLUSTERPORTAL)
2305 return qfalse;
2306 //the end position should be in area2, also test a little bit back
2307 //because the predicted jump could have rushed through the area
2308 VectorMA(move.endpos, -64, dir, teststart);
2309 teststart[2] += 1;
2310 numareas = AAS_TraceAreas(move.endpos, teststart, areas, NULL, ARRAY_LEN(areas));
2311 for (j = 0; j < numareas; j++)
2312 {
2313 if (areas[j] == area2num)
2314 break;
2315 } //end for
2316 if (j < numareas)
2317 break;
2318 }
2319 if (i >= 3)
2320 return qfalse;
2321 //
2322#ifdef REACH_DEBUG
2323 //create the reachability
2324 Log_Write("jump reachability between %d and %d\r\n", area1num, area2num);
2325#endif //REACH_DEBUG
2326 //create a new reachability link
2327 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
2328 if (!lreach) return qfalse;
2329 lreach->areanum = area2num;
2330 lreach->facenum = 0;
2331 lreach->edgenum = 0;
2332 VectorCopy(beststart, lreach->start);
2333 VectorCopy(bestend, lreach->end);
2334 lreach->traveltype = traveltype;
2335
2336 VectorSubtract(bestend, beststart, dir);
2337 height = dir[2];
2338 dir[2] = 0;
2339 if ((traveltype & TRAVELTYPE_MASK) == TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE && height > VectorLength(dir))
2340 {
2341 lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startwalkoffledge + height * 50 / aassettings.phys_gravity;
2342 }
2343 else
2344 {
2345 lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startjump + VectorDistance(bestend, beststart) * 240 / aassettings.phys_maxwalkvelocity;
2346 } //end if
2347 //
2348 if (!AAS_AreaJumpPad(area2num))
2349 {
2350 if (AAS_FallDelta(beststart[2] - bestend[2]) > aassettings.phys_falldelta5)
2351 {
2352 lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_falldamage5;
2353 } //end if
2354 else if (AAS_FallDelta(beststart[2] - bestend[2]) > aassettings.phys_falldelta10)
2355 {
2356 lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_falldamage10;
2357 } //end if
2358 } //end if
2359 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
2360 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
2361 //
2362 if ((traveltype & TRAVELTYPE_MASK) == TRAVEL_JUMP)
2363 reach_jump++;
2364 else
2365 reach_walkoffledge++;
2366 } //end if
2367 return qfalse;
2368} //end of the function AAS_Reachability_Jump
2369//===========================================================================
2370// create a possible ladder reachability from area1 to area2
2371//
2372// Parameter: -
2373// Returns: -
2374// Changes Globals: -
2375//===========================================================================
2376int AAS_Reachability_Ladder(int area1num, int area2num)
2377{
2378 int i, j, k, l, edge1num, edge2num, sharededgenum = 0, lowestedgenum = 0;
2379 int face1num, face2num, ladderface1num = 0, ladderface2num = 0;
2380 int ladderface1vertical, ladderface2vertical, firstv;
2381 float face1area, face2area, bestface1area = -9999, bestface2area = -9999;
2382 float phys_jumpvel, maxjumpheight;
2383 vec3_t area1point, area2point, v1, v2, up = {0, 0, 1};
2384 vec3_t mid, lowestpoint = {0, 0}, start, end, sharededgevec, dir;
2385 aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
2386 aas_face_t *face1, *face2, *ladderface1 = NULL, *ladderface2 = NULL;
2387 aas_plane_t *plane1, *plane2;
2388 aas_edge_t *sharededge, *edge1;
2389 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
2390 aas_trace_t trace;
2391
2392 if (!AAS_AreaLadder(area1num) || !AAS_AreaLadder(area2num)) return qfalse;
2393 //
2394 phys_jumpvel = aassettings.phys_jumpvel;
2395 //maximum height a player can jump with the given initial z velocity
2396 maxjumpheight = AAS_MaxJumpHeight(phys_jumpvel);
2397
2398 area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
2399 area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
2400
2401 for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
2402 {
2403 face1num = aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i];
2404 face1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face1num)];
2405 //if not a ladder face
2406 if (!(face1->faceflags & FACE_LADDER)) continue;
2407 //
2408 for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
2409 {
2410 face2num = aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j];
2411 face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face2num)];
2412 //if not a ladder face
2413 if (!(face2->faceflags & FACE_LADDER)) continue;
2414 //check if the faces share an edge
2415 for (k = 0; k < face1->numedges; k++)
2416 {
2417 edge1num = aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + k];
2418 for (l = 0; l < face2->numedges; l++)
2419 {
2420 edge2num = aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge + l];
2421 if (abs(edge1num) == abs(edge2num))
2422 {
2423 //get the face with the largest area
2424 face1area = AAS_FaceArea(face1);
2425 face2area = AAS_FaceArea(face2);
2426 if (face1area > bestface1area && face2area > bestface2area)
2427 {
2428 bestface1area = face1area;
2429 bestface2area = face2area;
2430 ladderface1 = face1;
2431 ladderface2 = face2;
2432 ladderface1num = face1num;
2433 ladderface2num = face2num;
2434 sharededgenum = edge1num;
2435 } //end if
2436 break;
2437 } //end if
2438 } //end for
2439 if (l != face2->numedges) break;
2440 } //end for
2441 } //end for
2442 } //end for
2443 //
2444 if (ladderface1 && ladderface2)
2445 {
2446 //get the middle of the shared edge
2447 sharededge = &aasworld.edges[abs(sharededgenum)];
2448 firstv = sharededgenum < 0;
2449 //
2450 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[sharededge->v[firstv]], v1);
2451 VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[sharededge->v[!firstv]], v2);
2452 VectorAdd(v1, v2, area1point);
2453 VectorScale(area1point, 0.5, area1point);
2454 VectorCopy(area1point, area2point);
2455 //
2456 //if the face plane in area 1 is pretty much vertical
2457 plane1 = &aasworld.planes[ladderface1->planenum ^ (ladderface1num < 0)];
2458 plane2 = &aasworld.planes[ladderface2->planenum ^ (ladderface2num < 0)];
2459 //
2460 //get the points really into the areas
2461 VectorSubtract(v2, v1, sharededgevec);
2462 CrossProduct(plane1->normal, sharededgevec, dir);
2463 VectorNormalize(dir);
2464 //NOTE: 32 because that's larger than 16 (bot bbox x,y)
2465 VectorMA(area1point, -32, dir, area1point);
2466 VectorMA(area2point, 32, dir, area2point);
2467 //
2468 ladderface1vertical = fabsf(DotProduct(plane1->normal, up)) < 0.1;
2469 ladderface2vertical = fabsf(DotProduct(plane2->normal, up)) < 0.1;
2470 //there's only reachability between vertical ladder faces
2471 if (!ladderface1vertical && !ladderface2vertical) return qfalse;
2472 //if both vertical ladder faces
2473 if (ladderface1vertical && ladderface2vertical
2474 //and the ladder faces do not make a sharp corner
2475 && DotProduct(plane1->normal, plane2->normal) > 0.7
2476 //and the shared edge is not too vertical
2477 && fabsf(DotProduct(sharededgevec, up)) < 0.7)
2478 {
2479 //create a new reachability link
2480 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
2481 if (!lreach) return qfalse;
2482 lreach->areanum = area2num;
2483 lreach->facenum = ladderface1num;
2484 lreach->edgenum = abs(sharededgenum);
2485 VectorCopy(area1point, lreach->start);

2722//===========================================================================
2723// create possible teleporter reachabilities
2724// this is very game dependent.... :(
2725//
2726// classname = trigger_multiple or trigger_teleport
2727// target = "t1"
2728//
2729// classname = target_teleporter
2730// targetname = "t1"
2731// target = "t2"
2732//
2733// classname = misc_teleporter_dest
2734// targetname = "t2"
2735//
2736// Parameter: -
2737// Returns: -
2738// Changes Globals: -
2739//===========================================================================
2740void AAS_Reachability_Teleport(void)
2741{
2742 int area1num, area2num;
2743 char target[MAX_EPAIRKEY], targetname[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
2744 char classname[MAX_EPAIRKEY], model[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
2745 int ent, dest;
2746 float angle;
2747 vec3_t origin, destorigin, mins, maxs, end, angles;
2748 vec3_t mid, velocity, cmdmove;
2749 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
2750 aas_clientmove_t move;
2751 aas_trace_t trace;
2752 aas_link_t *areas, *link;
2753
2754 for (ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent; ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent))
2755 {
2756 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "classname", classname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
2757 if (!strcmp(classname, "trigger_multiple"))
2758 {
2759 AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "model", model, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
2760//#ifdef REACH_DEBUG
2761 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_multiple model = \"%s\"\n", model);
2762//#endif REACH_DEBUG
2763 VectorClear(angles);
2764 AAS_BSPModelMinsMaxsOrigin(atoi(model+1), angles, mins, maxs, origin);
2765 //
2766 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2767 {
2768 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "trigger_multiple at %1.0f %1.0f %1.0f without target\n",
2769 origin[0], origin[1], origin[2]);
2770 continue;
2771 } //end if
2772 for (dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); dest; dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(dest))
2773 {
2774 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "classname", classname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
2775 if (!strcmp(classname, "target_teleporter"))
2776 {
2777 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "targetname", targetname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
2778 if (!strcmp(targetname, target))
2779 {
2780 break;
2781 } //end if
2782 } //end if
2783 } //end for
2784 if (!dest)
2785 {
2786 continue;
2787 } //end if
2788 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2789 {
2790 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "target_teleporter without target\n");
2791 continue;
2792 } //end if
2793 } //end else
2794 else if (!strcmp(classname, "trigger_teleport"))
2795 {
2796 AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "model", model, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
2797//#ifdef REACH_DEBUG
2798 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_teleport model = \"%s\"\n", model);
2799//#endif REACH_DEBUG
2800 VectorClear(angles);
2801 AAS_BSPModelMinsMaxsOrigin(atoi(model+1), angles, mins, maxs, origin);
2802 //
2803 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2804 {
2805 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "trigger_teleport at %1.0f %1.0f %1.0f without target\n",
2806 origin[0], origin[1], origin[2]);
2807 continue;
2808 } //end if
2809 } //end if
2810 else
2811 {
2812 continue;
2813 } //end else
2814 //
2815 for (dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); dest; dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(dest))
2816 {
2817 //classname should be misc_teleporter_dest
2818 //but I've also seen target_position and actually any
2819 //entity could be used... burp
2820 if (AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "targetname", targetname, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2821 {
2822 if (!strcmp(targetname, target))
2823 {
2824 break;
2825 } //end if
2826 } //end if
2827 } //end for
2828 if (!dest)
2829 {
2830 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "teleporter without misc_teleporter_dest (%s)\n", target);
2831 continue;
2832 } //end if
2833 if (!AAS_VectorForBSPEpairKey(dest, "origin", destorigin))
2834 {
2835 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "teleporter destination (%s) without origin\n", target);
2836 continue;
2837 } //end if
2838 //
2839 area2num = AAS_PointAreaNum(destorigin);
2840 //if not teleported into a teleporter or into a jumppad
2841 if (!AAS_AreaTeleporter(area2num) && !AAS_AreaJumpPad(area2num))
2842 {
2843 VectorCopy(destorigin, end);
2844 end[2] -= 64;
2845 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(destorigin, end, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
2846 if (trace.startsolid)
2847 {
2848 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "teleporter destination (%s) in solid\n", target);
2849 continue;
2850 } //end if
2851 /*
2852 area2num = AAS_PointAreaNum(trace.endpos);
2853 //
2854 if (!AAS_AreaTeleporter(area2num) &&
2855 !AAS_AreaJumpPad(area2num) &&
2856 !AAS_AreaGrounded(area2num))
2857 {
2858 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, destorigin);
2859 }
2860 else*/
2861 {
2862 //predict where you'll end up
2863 AAS_FloatForBSPEpairKey(dest, "angle", &angle);
2864 if (angle)
2865 {
2866 VectorSet(angles, 0, angle, 0);
2867 AngleVectors(angles, velocity, NULL, NULL);
2868 VectorScale(velocity, 400, velocity);
2869 } //end if
2870 else
2871 {
2872 VectorClear(velocity);
2873 } //end else
2874 VectorClear(cmdmove);
2875 AAS_PredictClientMovement(&move, -1, destorigin, PRESENCE_NORMAL, qfalse,
2876 velocity, cmdmove, 0, 30, 0.1f,
2877 SE_HITGROUND|SE_ENTERWATER|SE_ENTERSLIME|
2878 SE_ENTERLAVA|SE_HITGROUNDDAMAGE|SE_TOUCHJUMPPAD|SE_TOUCHTELEPORTER, 0, qfalse); //qtrue);
2879 area2num = AAS_PointAreaNum(move.endpos);
2880 if (move.stopevent & (SE_ENTERSLIME|SE_ENTERLAVA))
2881 {
2882 botimport.Print(PRT_WARNING, "teleported into slime or lava at dest %s\n", target);
2883 } //end if
2884 VectorCopy(move.endpos, destorigin);
2885 } //end else
2886 } //end if
2887 //
2888 //botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "teleporter brush origin at %f %f %f\n", origin[0], origin[1], origin[2]);
2889 //botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "teleporter brush mins = %f %f %f\n", mins[0], mins[1], mins[2]);
2890 //botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "teleporter brush maxs = %f %f %f\n", maxs[0], maxs[1], maxs[2]);
2891 VectorAdd(origin, mins, mins);
2892 VectorAdd(origin, maxs, maxs);
2893 //
2894 VectorAdd(mins, maxs, mid);
2895 VectorScale(mid, 0.5, mid);
2896 //link an invalid (-1) entity
2897 areas = AAS_LinkEntityClientBBox(mins, maxs, -1, PRESENCE_CROUCH);
2898 if (!areas) botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_multiple not in any area\n");
2899 //
2900 for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
2901 {
2902 //if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(link->areanum)) continue;
2903 if (!AAS_AreaTeleporter(link->areanum)) continue;
2904 //
2905 area1num = link->areanum;
2906 //create a new reachability link
2907 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
2908 if (!lreach) break;
2909 lreach->areanum = area2num;
2910 lreach->facenum = 0;
2911 lreach->edgenum = 0;
2912 VectorCopy(mid, lreach->start);
2913 VectorCopy(destorigin, lreach->end);
2914 lreach->traveltype = TRAVEL_TELEPORT;
2915 lreach->traveltype |= AAS_TravelFlagsForTeam(ent);
2916 lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_teleport;
2917 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
2918 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
2919 //
2920 reach_teleport++;
2921 } //end for
2922 //unlink the invalid entity
2923 AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
2924 } //end for
2925} //end of the function AAS_Reachability_Teleport
2926//===========================================================================
2927// create possible elevator (func_plat) reachabilities
2928// this is very game dependent.... :(
2929//
2930// Parameter: -
2931// Returns: -
2932// Changes Globals: -
2933//===========================================================================
2934void AAS_Reachability_Elevator(void)
2935{
2936 int area1num, area2num, modelnum, i, j, k, l, n, p;
2937 float lip, height, speed;
2938 char model[MAX_EPAIRKEY], classname[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
2939 int ent;
2940 vec3_t mins, maxs, origin, angles = {0, 0, 0};
2941 vec3_t pos1, pos2, mids, platbottom, plattop;
2942 vec3_t bottomorg, toporg, start, end, dir;
2943 vec_t xvals[8], yvals[8], xvals_top[8], yvals_top[8];
2944 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
2945 aas_trace_t trace;
2946
2947#ifdef REACH_DEBUG
2948 Log_Write("AAS_Reachability_Elevator\r\n");
2949#endif //REACH_DEBUG
2950 for (ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent; ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent))
2951 {
2952 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "classname", classname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
2953 if (!strcmp(classname, "func_plat"))
2954 {
2955#ifdef REACH_DEBUG
2956 Log_Write("found func plat\r\n");
2957#endif //REACH_DEBUG
2958 if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "model", model, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2959 {
2960 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "func_plat without model\n");
2961 continue;
2962 } //end if
2963 //get the model number, and skip the leading *
2964 modelnum = atoi(model+1);
2965 if (modelnum <= 0)
2966 {
2967 botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "func_plat with invalid model number\n");
2968 continue;
2969 } //end if
2970 //get the mins, maxs and origin of the model
2971 //NOTE: the origin is usually (0,0,0) and the mins and maxs
2972 // are the absolute mins and maxs
2973 AAS_BSPModelMinsMaxsOrigin(modelnum, angles, mins, maxs, origin);
2974 //
2975 AAS_VectorForBSPEpairKey(ent, "origin", origin);
2976 //pos1 is the top position, pos2 is the bottom
2977 VectorCopy(origin, pos1);
2978 VectorCopy(origin, pos2);
2979 //get the lip of the plat
2980 AAS_FloatForBSPEpairKey(ent, "lip", &lip);
2981 if (!lip) lip = 8;
2982 //get the movement height of the plat
2983 AAS_FloatForBSPEpairKey(ent, "height", &height);
2984 if (!height) height = (maxs[2] - mins[2]) - lip;
2985 //get the speed of the plat
2986 AAS_FloatForBSPEpairKey(ent, "speed", &speed);
2987 if (!speed) speed = 200;
2988 //get bottom position below pos1
2989 pos2[2] -= height;
2990 //
2991 //get a point just above the plat in the bottom position
2992 VectorAdd(mins, maxs, mids);
2993 VectorMA(pos2, 0.5, mids, platbottom);
2994 platbottom[2] = maxs[2] - (pos1[2] - pos2[2]) + 2;
2995 //get a point just above the plat in the top position
2996 VectorAdd(mins, maxs, mids);
2997 VectorMA(pos2, 0.5, mids, plattop);
2998 plattop[2] = maxs[2] + 2;
2999 //
3000 /*if (!area1num)
3001 {
3002 Log_Write("no grounded area near plat bottom\r\n");
3003 continue;
3004 } //end if*/
3005 //get the mins and maxs a little larger
3006 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
3007 {
3008 mins[i] -= 1;
3009 maxs[i] += 1;
3010 } //end for
3011 //
3012 //botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "platbottom[2] = %1.1f plattop[2] = %1.1f\n", platbottom[2], plattop[2]);
3013 //
3014 VectorAdd(mins, maxs, mids);
3015 VectorScale(mids, 0.5, mids);
3016 //
3017 xvals[0] = mins[0]; xvals[1] = mids[0]; xvals[2] = maxs[0]; xvals[3] = mids[0];
3018 yvals[0] = mids[1]; yvals[1] = maxs[1]; yvals[2] = mids[1]; yvals[3] = mins[1];
3019 //
3020 xvals[4] = mins[0]; xvals[5] = maxs[0]; xvals[6] = maxs[0]; xvals[7] = mins[0];
3021 yvals[4] = maxs[1]; yvals[5] = maxs[1]; yvals[6] = mins[1]; yvals[7] = mins[1];
3022 //find adjacent areas around the bottom of the plat
3023 for (i = 0; i < 9; i++)
3024 {
3025 if (i < 8) //check at the sides of the plat
3026 {
3027 bottomorg[0] = origin[0] + xvals[i];
3028 bottomorg[1] = origin[1] + yvals[i];
3029 bottomorg[2] = platbottom[2] + 16;
3030 //get a grounded or swim area near the plat in the bottom position
3031 area1num = AAS_PointAreaNum(bottomorg);
3032 for (k = 0; k < 16; k++)
3033 {
3034 if (area1num)
3035 {
3036 if (AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) || AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) break;
3037 } //end if
3038 bottomorg[2] += 4;
3039 area1num = AAS_PointAreaNum(bottomorg);
3040 } //end if
3041 //if in solid
3042 if (k >= 16)
3043 {
3044 continue;
3045 } //end if
3046 } //end if
3047 else //at the middle of the plat
3048 {
3049 VectorCopy(plattop, bottomorg);
3050 bottomorg[2] += 24;
3051 area1num = AAS_PointAreaNum(bottomorg);
3052 if (!area1num) continue;
3053 VectorCopy(platbottom, bottomorg);
3054 bottomorg[2] += 24;
3055 } //end else
3056 //look at adjacent areas around the top of the plat
3057 //make larger steps to outside the plat everytime
3058 for (n = 0; n < 3; n++)
3059 {
3060 for (k = 0; k < 3; k++)
3061 {
3062 mins[k] -= 4;
3063 maxs[k] += 4;
3064 } //end for
3065 xvals_top[0] = mins[0]; xvals_top[1] = mids[0]; xvals_top[2] = maxs[0]; xvals_top[3] = mids[0];

3086 VectorCopy(toporg, end);

3094 } //end if

3101 //if there already exists reachability between the areas
3102 if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(area1num, area2num)) continue;
3103 //if the reachability start is within the elevator bounding box
3104 VectorSubtract(bottomorg, platbottom, dir);
3105 VectorNormalize(dir);
3106 dir[0] = bottomorg[0] + 24 * dir[0];
3107 dir[1] = bottomorg[1] + 24 * dir[1];
3108 dir[2] = bottomorg[2];
3109 //
3110 for (p = 0; p < 3; p++)
3111 if (dir[p] < origin[p] + mins[p] || dir[p] > origin[p] + maxs[p]) break;
3112 if (p >= 3) continue;

3114 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();

3117 //the facenum is the model number

3121 //

3126 lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startelevator + height * 100 / speed;
3127 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
3128 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
3129 //don't go any further to the outside
3130 n = 9999;
3131 //

3134#endif //REACH_DEBUG
3135 //

3137 } //end for
3138 } //end for
3139 } //end for

3141 } //end for

3144//
3145// Parameter: -
3146// Returns: -

3148//===========================================================================
3149aas_lreachability_t *AAS_FindFaceReachabilities(vec3_t *facepoints, int numpoints, aas_plane_t *plane, int towardsface)
3150{
3151 int i, j, k, l;
3152 int facenum, edgenum, bestfacenum;
3153 float *v1, *v2, *v3, *v4;
3154 float bestdist, speed, hordist, dist;
3155 vec3_t beststart = {0}, beststart2 = {0}, bestend = {0}, bestend2 = {0}, tmp, hordir, testpoint;
3156 aas_lreachability_t *lreach, *lreachabilities;
3157 aas_area_t *area;
3158 aas_face_t *face;
3159 aas_edge_t *edge;
3160 aas_plane_t *faceplane, *bestfaceplane;
3161
3162 //
3163 lreachabilities = NULL;
3164 bestfacenum = 0;
3165 bestfaceplane = NULL;
3166 //
3167 for (i = 1; i < aasworld.numareas; i++)
3168 {
3169 area = &aasworld.areas[i];
3170 // get the shortest distance between one of the func_bob start edges and
3171 // one of the face edges of area1
3172 bestdist = 999999;
3173 for (j = 0; j < area->numfaces; j++)
3174 {
3175 facenum = aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + j];
3176 face = &aasworld.faces[abs(facenum)];
3177 //if not a ground face
3178 if (!(face->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
3179 //get the ground planes
3180 faceplane = &aasworld.planes[face->planenum];
3181 //
3182 for (k = 0; k < face->numedges; k++)
3183 {
3184 edgenum = abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge + k]);
3185 edge = &aasworld.edges[edgenum];
3186 //calculate the minimum distance between the two edges
3187 v1 = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]];
3188 v2 = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]];
3189 //
3190 for (l = 0; l < numpoints; l++)
3191 {
3192 v3 = facepoints[l];
3193 v4 = facepoints[(l+1) % numpoints];
3194 dist = AAS_ClosestEdgePoints(v1, v2, v3, v4, faceplane, plane,
3195 beststart, bestend,
3196 beststart2, bestend2, bestdist);
3197 if (dist < bestdist)
3198 {
3199 bestfacenum = facenum;
3200 bestfaceplane = faceplane;
3201 bestdist = dist;
3202 } //end if
3203 } //end for
3204 } //end for
3205 } //end for
3206 //
3207 if (bestdist > 192) continue;
3208 //
3209 VectorMiddle(beststart, beststart2, beststart);
3210 VectorMiddle(bestend, bestend2, bestend);
3211 //
3212 if (!towardsface)
3213 {
3214 VectorCopy(beststart, tmp);
3215 VectorCopy(bestend, beststart);
3216 VectorCopy(tmp, bestend);
3217 } //end if
3218 //
3219 VectorSubtract(bestend, beststart, hordir);
3220 hordir[2] = 0;
3221 hordist = VectorLength(hordir);
3222 //
3223 if (hordist > 2 * AAS_MaxJumpDistance(aassettings.phys_jumpvel)) continue;
3224 //the end point should not be significantly higher than the start point
3225 if (bestend[2] - 32 > beststart[2]) continue;
3226 //don't fall down too far
3227 if (bestend[2] < beststart[2] - 128) continue;
3228 //the distance should not be too far
3229 if (hordist > 32)
3230 {
3231 //check for walk off ledge
3232 if (!AAS_HorizontalVelocityForJump(0, beststart, bestend, &speed)) continue;
3233 } //end if
3234 //
3235 beststart[2] += 1;
3236 bestend[2] += 1;
3237 //
3238 if (towardsface) VectorCopy(bestend, testpoint);
3239 else VectorCopy(beststart, testpoint);
3240 if (bestfaceplane != NULL)
3241 testpoint[2] = (bestfaceplane->dist - DotProduct(bestfaceplane->normal, testpoint)) / bestfaceplane->normal[2];
3242 else
3243 testpoint[2] = 0;
3244 //
3245 if (!AAS_PointInsideFace(bestfacenum, testpoint, 0.1f))
3246 {
3247 //if the faces are not overlapping then only go down
3248 if (bestend[2] - 16 > beststart[2]) continue;
3249 } //end if
3250 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
3251 if (!lreach) return lreachabilities;
3252 lreach->areanum = i;
3253 lreach->facenum = 0;
3254 lreach->edgenum = 0;
3255 VectorCopy(beststart, lreach->start);
3256 VectorCopy(bestend, lreach->end);
3257 lreach->traveltype = 0;
3258 lreach->traveltime = 0;
3259 lreach->next = lreachabilities;
3260 lreachabilities = lreach;
3261#ifndef BSPC
3262 if (towardsface) AAS_PermanentLine(lreach->start, lreach->end, 1);
3263 else AAS_PermanentLine(lreach->start, lreach->end, 2);
3264#endif
3265 } //end for
3266 return lreachabilities;
3267} //end of the function AAS_FindFaceReachabilities

3774//===========================================================================
3775// never point at ground faces
3776// always a higher and pretty far area
3777//
3778// Parameter: -
3779// Returns: -
3780// Changes Globals: -
3781//===========================================================================
3782int AAS_Reachability_Grapple(int area1num, int area2num)
3783{
3784 int face2num, i, j, areanum, numareas, areas[20];
3785 float mingrappleangle, z, hordist;
3786 bsp_trace_t bsptrace;
3787 aas_trace_t trace;
3788 aas_face_t *face2;
3789 aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
3790 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
3791 vec3_t areastart = {0, 0, 0}, facecenter, start, end, dir, down = {0, 0, -1};
3792 vec_t *v;
3793
3794 //only grapple when on the ground or swimming
3795 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) && !AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) return qfalse;
3796 //don't grapple from a crouch area
3797 if (!(AAS_AreaPresenceType(area1num) & PRESENCE_NORMAL)) return qfalse;
3798 //NOTE: disabled area swim it doesn't work right
3799 if (AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) return qfalse;
3800 //
3801 area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
3802 area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
3803 //don't grapple towards way lower areas
3804 if (area2->maxs[2] < area1->mins[2]) return qfalse;
3805 //
3806 VectorCopy(aasworld.areas[area1num].center, start);
3807 //if not a swim area
3808 if (!AAS_AreaSwim(area1num))
3809 {
3810 if (!AAS_PointAreaNum(start)) Log_Write("area %d center %f %f %f in solid?\r\n", area1num,
3811 start[0], start[1], start[2]);
3812 VectorCopy(start, end);
3813 end[2] -= 1000;
3814 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
3815 if (trace.startsolid) return qfalse;
3816 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, areastart);
3817 } //end if
3818 else
3819 {
3820 if (!(AAS_PointContents(start) & (CONTENTS_LAVA|CONTENTS_SLIME|CONTENTS_WATER))) return qfalse;
3821 } //end else
3822 //
3823 //start is now the start point
3824 //
3825 for (i = 0; i < area2->numfaces; i++)
3826 {
3827 face2num = aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + i];
3828 face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face2num)];
3829 //if it is not a solid face
3830 if (!(face2->faceflags & FACE_SOLID)) continue;
3831 //direction towards the first vertex of the face
3832 v = aasworld.vertexes[aasworld.edges[abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge])].v[0]];
3833 VectorSubtract(v, areastart, dir);
3834 //if the face plane is facing away
3835 if (DotProduct(aasworld.planes[face2->planenum].normal, dir) > 0) continue;
3836 //get the center of the face
3837 AAS_FaceCenter(face2num, facecenter);
3838 //only go higher up with the grapple
3839 if (facecenter[2] < areastart[2] + 64) continue;
3840 //only use vertical faces or downward facing faces
3841 if (DotProduct(aasworld.planes[face2->planenum].normal, down) < 0) continue;
3842 //direction towards the face center
3843 VectorSubtract(facecenter, areastart, dir);
3844 //
3845 z = dir[2];
3846 dir[2] = 0;
3847 hordist = VectorLength(dir);
3848 if (!hordist) continue;
3849 //if too far
3850 if (hordist > 2000) continue;
3851 //check the minimal angle of the movement
3852 mingrappleangle = 15; //15 degrees
3853 if (z / hordist < tan(2 * M_PI * mingrappleangle / 360)) continue;
3854 //
3855 VectorCopy(facecenter, start);
3856 VectorMA(facecenter, -500, aasworld.planes[face2->planenum].normal, end);
3857 //
3858 bsptrace = AAS_Trace(start, NULL, NULL, end, 0, CONTENTS_SOLID);
3859 //the grapple won't stick to the sky and the grapple point should be near the AAS wall
3860 if ((bsptrace.surface.flags & SURF_SKY) || (bsptrace.fraction * 500 > 32)) continue;
3861 //trace a full bounding box from the area center on the ground to
3862 //the center of the face
3863 VectorSubtract(facecenter, areastart, dir);
3864 VectorNormalize(dir);
3865 VectorMA(areastart, 4, dir, start);
3866 VectorCopy(bsptrace.endpos, end);
3867 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_NORMAL, -1);
3868 VectorSubtract(trace.endpos, facecenter, dir);
3869 if (VectorLength(dir) > 24) continue;
3870 //
3871 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, start);
3872 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, end);
3873 end[2] -= AAS_FallDamageDistance();
3874 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_NORMAL, -1);
3875 if (trace.fraction >= 1) continue;
3876 //area to end in
3877 areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(trace.endpos);
3878 //if not in lava or slime
3879 if (aasworld.areasettings[areanum].contents & (AREACONTENTS_SLIME|AREACONTENTS_LAVA))
3880 {
3881 continue;
3882 } //end if
3883 //do not go the the source area
3884 if (areanum == area1num) continue;
3885 //don't create reachabilities if they already exist
3886 if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(area1num, areanum)) continue;
3887 //only end in areas we can stand
3888 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(areanum)) continue;
3889 //never go through cluster portals!!
3890 numareas = AAS_TraceAreas(areastart, bsptrace.endpos, areas, NULL, 20);
3891 if (numareas >= 20) continue;
3892 for (j = 0; j < numareas; j++)
3893 {
3894 if (aasworld.areasettings[areas[j]].contents & AREACONTENTS_CLUSTERPORTAL) break;
3895 } //end for
3896 if (j < numareas) continue;
3897 //create a new reachability link
3898 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
3899 if (!lreach) return qfalse;
3900 lreach->areanum = areanum;
3901 lreach->facenum = face2num;
3902 lreach->edgenum = 0;
3903 VectorCopy(areastart, lreach->start);
3904 //VectorCopy(facecenter, lreach->end);
3905 VectorCopy(bsptrace.endpos, lreach->end);
3906 lreach->traveltype = TRAVEL_GRAPPLEHOOK;
3907 VectorSubtract(lreach->end, lreach->start, dir);
3908 lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startgrapple + VectorLength(dir) * 0.25;
3909 lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
3910 areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
3911 //
3912 reach_grapple++;
3913 } //end for
3914 //
3915 return qfalse;
3916} //end of the function AAS_Reachability_Grapple

4114//===========================================================================

4121void AAS_Reachability_WalkOffLedge(int areanum)
4122{

4124 int face1num, face2num, face3num, edge1num, edge2num, edge3num;
4125 int otherareanum, gap, reachareanum, side;

4129 aas_plane_t *plane;
