4132 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
4133 aas_trace_t trace;
4134
4135 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(areanum) || AAS_AreaSwim(areanum)) return;
4136 //
4137 area = &aasworld.areas[areanum];
4138 //
4139 for (i = 0; i < area->numfaces; i++)
4140 {
4141 face1num = aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + i];
4142 face1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face1num)];
4143 //face 1 must be a ground face
4144 if (!(face1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
4145 //go through all the edges of this ground face
4146 for (k = 0; k < face1->numedges; k++)
4147 {
4148 edge1num = aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + k];
4149 //find another not ground face using this same edge
4150 for (j = 0; j < area->numfaces; j++)
4151 {
4152 face2num = aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + j];
4153 face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face2num)];
4154 //face 2 may not be a ground face
4155 if (face2->faceflags & FACE_GROUND) continue;
4156 //compare all the edges
4157 for (l = 0; l < face2->numedges; l++)
4158 {
4159 edge2num = aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge + l];
4160 if (abs(edge1num) == abs(edge2num))
4161 {
4162 //get the area at the other side of the face
4163 if (face2->frontarea == areanum) otherareanum = face2->backarea;
4164 else otherareanum = face2->frontarea;
4165 //
4166 area2 = &aasworld.areas[otherareanum];
4167 //if the other area is grounded!
4168 if (aasworld.areasettings[otherareanum].areaflags & AREA_GROUNDED)
4169 {
4170 //check for a possible gap
4171 gap = qfalse;
4172 for (n = 0; n < area2->numfaces; n++)
4173 {
4174 face3num = aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + n];
4175 //may not be the shared face of the two areas
4176 if (abs(face3num) == abs(face2num)) continue;
4177 //
4178 face3 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face3num)];
4179 //find an edge shared by all three faces
4180 for (m = 0; m < face3->numedges; m++)
4181 {
4182 edge3num = aasworld.edgeindex[face3->firstedge + m];
4183 //but the edge should be shared by all three faces
4184 if (abs(edge3num) == abs(edge1num))
4185 {
4186 if (!(face3->faceflags & FACE_SOLID))
4187 {
4188 gap = qtrue;
4189 break;
4190 } //end if
4191 //
4192 if (face3->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)
4193 {
4194 gap = qfalse;
4195 break;
4196 } //end if
4197 //FIXME: there are more situations to be handled
4198 gap = qtrue;
4199 break;
4200 } //end if
4201 } //end for
4202 if (m < face3->numedges) break;
4203 } //end for
4204 if (!gap) break;
4205 } //end if
4206 //check for a walk off ledge reachability
4207 edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edge1num)];
4208 side = edge1num < 0;
4209 //
4210 v1 = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]];
4211 v2 = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[!side]];
4212 //
4213 plane = &aasworld.planes[face1->planenum];
4214 //get the points really into the areas
4215 VectorSubtract(v2, v1, sharededgevec);
4216 CrossProduct(plane->normal, sharededgevec, dir);
4217 VectorNormalize(dir);
4218 //
4219 VectorAdd(v1, v2, mid);
4220 VectorScale(mid, 0.5, mid);
4221 VectorMA(mid, 8, dir, mid);
4222 //
4223 VectorCopy(mid, testend);
4224 testend[2] -= 1000;
4225 trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(mid, testend, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
4226 //
4227 if (trace.startsolid)
4228 {
4229 //Log_Write("area %d: trace.startsolid\r\n", areanum);
4230 break;
4231 } //end if
4232 reachareanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(trace.endpos);
4233 if (reachareanum == areanum)
4234 {
4235 //Log_Write("area %d: same area\r\n", areanum);
4236 break;
4237 } //end if
4238 if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(areanum, reachareanum))
4239 {
4240 //Log_Write("area %d: reachability already exists\r\n", areanum);
4241 break;
4242 } //end if
4243 if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(reachareanum) && !AAS_AreaSwim(reachareanum))
4244 {
4245 //Log_Write("area %d, reach area %d: not grounded and not swim\r\n", areanum, reachareanum);
4246 break;
4247 } //end if
4248 //
4249 if (aasworld.areasettings[reachareanum].contents & (AREACONTENTS_SLIME
4250 | AREACONTENTS_LAVA))
4251 {
4252 //Log_Write("area %d, reach area %d: lava or slime\r\n", areanum, reachareanum);
4253 break;
4254 } //end if
4255 //if not going through a cluster portal
4256 numareas = AAS_TraceAreas(mid, testend, areas, NULL, ARRAY_LEN(areas));
4257 for (p = 0; p < numareas; p++)
4258 if (AAS_AreaClusterPortal(areas[p]))
4259 break;
4260 if (p < numareas)
4261 break;
4262 // if a maximum fall height is set and the bot would fall down further
4263 if (aassettings.rs_maxfallheight && fabs(mid[2] - trace.endpos[2]) > aassettings.rs_maxfallheight)
4264 break;
4265 //
4266 lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
4267 if (!lreach) break;
4268 lreach->areanum = reachareanum;
4269 lreach->facenum = 0;
4270 lreach->edgenum = edge1num;
4271 VectorCopy(mid, lreach->start);
4272 VectorCopy(trace.endpos, lreach->end);
4273 lreach->traveltype = TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE;
4274 lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startwalkoffledge + fabs(mid[2] - trace.endpos[2]) * 50 / aassettings.phys_gravity;
4275 if (!AAS_AreaSwim(reachareanum) && !AAS_AreaJumpPad(reachareanum))
4276 {
4277 if (AAS_FallDelta(mid[2] - trace.endpos[2]) > aassettings.phys_falldelta5)
4278 {
4279 lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_falldamage5;
4280 } //end if
4281 else if (AAS_FallDelta(mid[2] - trace.endpos[2]) > aassettings.phys_falldelta10)
4282 {
4283 lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_falldamage10;
4284 } //end if
4285 } //end if
4286 lreach->next = areareachability[areanum];
4287 areareachability[areanum] = lreach;
4288 //we've got another walk off ledge reachability
4289 reach_walkoffledge++;
4290 } //end if
4291 } //end for
4292 } //end for
4293 } //end for
4294 } //end for
4295} //end of the function AAS_Reachability_WalkOffLedge

4302void AAS_StoreReachability(void)

4304 int i;
4305 aas_areasettings_t *areasettings;
4306 aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
4307 aas_reachability_t *reach;
4308
4309 if (aasworld.reachability) FreeMemory(aasworld.reachability);
4310 aasworld.reachability = (aas_reachability_t *) GetClearedMemory((numlreachabilities + 10) * sizeof(aas_reachability_t));
4311 aasworld.reachabilitysize = 1;
4312 for (i = 0; i < aasworld.numareas; i++)
4313 {
4314 areasettings = &aasworld.areasettings[i];
4315 areasettings->firstreachablearea = aasworld.reachabilitysize;
4316 areasettings->numreachableareas = 0;
4317 for (lreach = areareachability[i]; lreach; lreach = lreach->next)
4318 {
4319 reach = &aasworld.reachability[areasettings->firstreachablearea +
4320 areasettings->numreachableareas];
4321 reach->areanum = lreach->areanum;
4322 reach->facenum = lreach->facenum;
4323 reach->edgenum = lreach->edgenum;
4324 VectorCopy(lreach->start, reach->start);
4325 VectorCopy(lreach->end, reach->end);
4326 reach->traveltype = lreach->traveltype;
4327 reach->traveltime = lreach->traveltime;
4328 //
4329 areasettings->numreachableareas++;
4330 } //end for
4331 aasworld.reachabilitysize += areasettings->numreachableareas;
4332 } //end for

4335//
4336// TRAVEL_WALK 100% equal floor height + steps
4337// TRAVEL_CROUCH 100%

4340// TRAVEL_LADDER 100% + fall down from ladder + jump up to ladder
4341// TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE 90% walk off very steep walls?
4342// TRAVEL_SWIM 100%

4349// TRAVEL_STRAFEJUMP 0%
4350// TRAVEL_ROCKETJUMP 100% (currently limited towards areas with items)
4351// TRAVEL_BFGJUMP 0% (currently disabled)
4352// TRAVEL_JUMPPAD 100%
4353// TRAVEL_FUNCBOB 100%
4354//
4355// Parameter: -
4356// Returns: true if NOT finished

4359int AAS_ContinueInitReachability(float time)
4360{
4361 int i, j, todo, start_time;
4362 static float framereachability, reachability_delay;
4363 static int lastpercentage;
4364
4365 if (!aasworld.loaded) return qfalse;
4366 //if reachability is calculated for all areas
4367 if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas >= aasworld.numareas + 2) return qfalse;
4368 //if starting with area 1 (area 0 is a dummy)
4369 if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas == 1)
4370 {
4371 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "calculating reachability...\n");
4372 lastpercentage = 0;
4373 framereachability = 2000;
4374 reachability_delay = 1000;
4375 } //end if
4376 //number of areas to calculate reachability for this cycle
4377 todo = aasworld.numreachabilityareas + (int) framereachability;
4378 start_time = Sys_MilliSeconds();
4379 //loop over the areas
4380 for (i = aasworld.numreachabilityareas; i < aasworld.numareas && i < todo; i++)
4381 {
4382 aasworld.numreachabilityareas++;
4383 //only create jumppad reachabilities from jumppad areas
4384 if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD)
4385 {
4386 continue;
4387 } //end if
4388 //loop over the areas
4389 for (j = 1; j < aasworld.numareas; j++)
4390 {
4391 if (i == j) continue;
4392 //never create reachabilities from teleporter or jumppad areas to regular areas
4393 if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & (AREACONTENTS_TELEPORTER|AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD))
4394 {
4395 if (!(aasworld.areasettings[j].contents & (AREACONTENTS_TELEPORTER|AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD)))
4396 {
4397 continue;
4398 } //end if
4399 } //end if
4400 //if there already is a reachability link from area i to j
4401 if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(i, j)) continue;
4402 //check for a swim reachability
4403 if (AAS_Reachability_Swim(i, j)) continue;
4404 //check for a simple walk on equal floor height reachability
4405 if (AAS_Reachability_EqualFloorHeight(i, j)) continue;
4406 //check for step, barrier, waterjump and walk off ledge reachabilities
4407 if (AAS_Reachability_Step_Barrier_WaterJump_WalkOffLedge(i, j)) continue;
4408 //check for ladder reachabilities
4409 if (AAS_Reachability_Ladder(i, j)) continue;
4410 //check for a jump reachability
4411 if (AAS_Reachability_Jump(i, j)) continue;
4412 } //end for
4413 //never create these reachabilities from teleporter or jumppad areas
4414 if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & (AREACONTENTS_TELEPORTER|AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD))
4415 {
4416 continue;
4417 } //end if
4418 //loop over the areas
4419 for (j = 1; j < aasworld.numareas; j++)
4420 {
4421 if (i == j) continue;
4422 //
4423 if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(i, j)) continue;
4424 //check for a grapple hook reachability
4425 if (calcgrapplereach) AAS_Reachability_Grapple(i, j);
4426 //check for a weapon jump reachability
4427 AAS_Reachability_WeaponJump(i, j);
4428 } //end for
4429 //if the calculation took more time than the max reachability delay
4430 if (Sys_MilliSeconds() - start_time > (int) reachability_delay) break;
4431 //
4432 if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas * 1000 / aasworld.numareas > lastpercentage) break;
4433 } //end for
4434 //
4435 if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas == aasworld.numareas)
4436 {
4437 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "\r%6.1f%%", (float) 100.0);
4438 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "\nplease wait while storing reachability...\n");
4439 aasworld.numreachabilityareas++;
4440 } //end if
4441 //if this is the last step in the reachability calculations
4442 else if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas == aasworld.numareas + 1)
4443 {
4444 //create additional walk off ledge reachabilities for every area
4445 for (i = 1; i < aasworld.numareas; i++)
4446 {
4447 //only create jumppad reachabilities from jumppad areas
4448 if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD)
4449 {
4450 continue;
4451 } //end if
4452 AAS_Reachability_WalkOffLedge(i);
4453 } //end for
4454 //create jump pad reachabilities
4455 AAS_Reachability_JumpPad();
4456 //create teleporter reachabilities
4457 AAS_Reachability_Teleport();
4458 //create elevator (func_plat) reachabilities
4459 AAS_Reachability_Elevator();
4460 //create func_bobbing reachabilities
4461 AAS_Reachability_FuncBobbing();
4462 //
4463#ifdef DEBUG
4464 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach swim\n", reach_swim);
4465 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach equal floor\n", reach_equalfloor);
4466 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach step\n", reach_step);
4467 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach barrier\n", reach_barrier);
4468 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach waterjump\n", reach_waterjump);
4469 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach walkoffledge\n", reach_walkoffledge);
4470 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach jump\n", reach_jump);
4471 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach ladder\n", reach_ladder);
4472 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach walk\n", reach_walk);
4473 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach teleport\n", reach_teleport);
4474 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach funcbob\n", reach_funcbob);
4475 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach elevator\n", reach_elevator);
4476 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach grapple\n", reach_grapple);
4477 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach rocketjump\n", reach_rocketjump);
4478 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "%6d reach jumppad\n", reach_jumppad);
4479#endif
4480 //*/
4481 //store all the reachabilities
4482 AAS_StoreReachability();
4483 //free the reachability link heap
4484 AAS_ShutDownReachabilityHeap();
4485 //
4486 FreeMemory(areareachability);
4487 //
4488 aasworld.numreachabilityareas++;
4489 //
4490 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "calculating clusters...\n");
4491 } //end if
4492 else
4493 {
4494 lastpercentage = aasworld.numreachabilityareas * 1000 / aasworld.numareas;
4495 botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "\r%6.1f%%", (float) lastpercentage / 10);
